<span class="header1">ENVIRONMENT</span>
<p>There are occupations that mix a love for the outdoors and an interest in technology.  Here are three examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Meteorologist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AF/1265.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Meteorologist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Meteorologists use computers, radar and satellites to study the atmosphere.  As a meteorologist, you would use the data you collect to create weather reports.  These reports tell people about current conditions.  They also forecast future weather conditions.  This is an important job.  Weather forecasts are used to warn  people of severe or dangerous weather.  This information is important to everybody.  It can help to save lives.  It can also help to save property.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a degree in meteorology, or in a related field such as physics or earth science.  If you want to teach meteorology or conduct research, you would need a Master's Degree or Ph.D.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary is between $30,000 to $92,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Agricultural Technician</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AF/1194.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Agricultural Technician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>An agricultural technician works closely with agricultural scientists.  If you were an agricultural technician, you would help these scientists to increase plant production.  You would also help to see that farm animals were well fed.  You would spend time in the laboratory and at local farms.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a two-year degree in agriculture from a technical or community college.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $15,000 to $40,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Landscaper</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/AF/43190.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Landscaper" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Landscapers spend nearly all of their time outdoors.  If you were a landscaper, you might work as a gardener or groundskeeper.  You would seed, weed, mow, fertilize grass, and fertilize and prune shrubs using the many tools of the landscaping trade. This is a good occupation if you want a business of your own.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a high school diploma.  If you want to supervise other landscapers, you need some college courses in horticulture and landscaping experience. Many landscapers work for themselves.  So, it is helpful to understand how a small business works.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>A landscaper can make anywhere from $11,000 to $24,000 a year.</blockquote>

